Description: Absolute pandomonium at the Stade de La Beaujoire! The XF (Expected Fume) for this one was high and there was serious bang delivered for the ‚Ç¨25 ticket price. First of all, great to see #Barclaysman royalty in the form of Andr√© Ayew leading the line for Le Havre. #Toxicity levels immediately spiked after Le Havre took the lead after 2 minutes. Game delayed for 10 minutes right after the Ultras threw toilet paper and tennis balls on the pitch during a Le Havre corner. Things were getting tasty but that was only a hint of what was to come, more on that later. I was sitting there watching a few stewards pick up tennis balls and bog roll and I‚Äòm sitting there thinking that there are worse ideas than having a few Labradors on hand to clean things up. Anyway, about 70 minutes of absolutely diabolical passed when Le Havre doubled the lead, things were about to get seriously tasty. In the dying embers of injury time, about 100 ultras in yellow balaclavas hopped the fence and I saw one of them headbutting a riot shield which was very funny, he immediately got 7 buckets of shit kicked out of him by about 4 riot shields.. Another delay of game and a solid 10 minute display of skirmishes and #CivilUnrest, it was an authentic French cultural experience. The referee eventually just decided to fuck it all off, blew his whistle and ran like fuck down the tunnel, ending any last hope of seeing the last 40 seconds played out. The skirmish eventually subsided and some fatty in a yellow balaclava took his opportunity to waffle into the loudspeaker whilst me, and about 10,000 other punters, took this as the cue to head for the exits. You had me with headbutting riot shields, you lost me when you tried to give a speech into a loudspeaker while wearing a yellow balaclava. Onto the negatives: the food options were lackluster to say the least, I expect greater options that Fromage Sandwiches and Jambon Sandwiches. The stadium was also bleeding baltic cold but I‚Äòm willing to hold my hand up and say that there‚Äòs not much to be done about that. I have a serious case of Uber Eats Ligue 1 McDonalds fever.
